description:
Dark Cities (Les Cités obscures in French), is a series of fantasy-themed comic, created by Belgian cartoonist and scriptwriter François Schuiten French Benoît Peeters in 1983 with Les murailles Samaris (The walls of Samaris) and continues to be published today, having appeared a dozen comic albums and many other related products, from picture books to fake documentaries on DVD.

The series is set in an imaginary continent located in a parallel world, in principle invisible to us, which are mixed multitude of influences, from Borgesian metaphysical surrealism to literature by Jules Verne (mainly their extraordinary journeys). The series highlights the detailed architectural designs for different cities Schuiten dark, which are mostly versions reinterpretations or "dark" real cities like Brussels or Pâhry Brusel Paris.
name: Las ciudades oscuras

Maybe it was fate that brought them together that day but Taichi met Kokoro when she literally fell from the sky. Waking up in the hospital, he begins to see Kokoro's spirit and after roaming the hospital premises a "shinigami" arrives to take Kokoro to the underworld. Is this the end for Kokoro? description:
A legendary love that started small. The Hulk can find enemies anywhere, even on a sub-molecular level - but love long eluded him until his atom-shattering romance with Jarella! The tiniest of worlds offered him all that he ever desired - but when the Hulk fights his way through obstacles on both Earth and K'ai, what will be left waiting for him? Collecting INCREDIBLE HULK #140, #148, #156, #202-203, #205-207, #246-248; THE AVENGERS #88 and WHAT IF? #23.

Note: The contents differ slightly to the previously released Hulk: Heart of the Atom trade. This collection presents (heavily edited) issues that were previously not printed due to licensing issues with ROM and the Micronauts.
name: Hulk: Heart of the Atom
